## Description {#details}

This file defines the SparseMultiSet class, which adds multiset behavior to the SparseSet.

A sparse multiset holds a small number of objects identified by integer keys from a moderately sized universe. The sparse multiset uses more memory than other containers in order to provide faster operations. Any key can map to multiple values. A SparseMultiSetNode class is provided, which serves as a convenient base class for the contents of a SparseMultiSet.

<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Compared to DenseSet and DenseMap, SparseMultiSet provides constant-time</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// fast clear() as fast as a vector.  The find(), insert(), and erase()</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// operations are all constant time, and typically faster than a hash table.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The iteration order doesn&#39;t depend on numerical key values, it only depends</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// on the order of insert() and erase() operations.  Iteration order is the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// insertion order. Iteration is only provided over elements of equivalent</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// keys, but iterators are bidirectional.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// array holding indexes into the dense vector.  Most of the memory is used by</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Multiset behavior is provided by providing doubly linked lists for values</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="442"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Erases an existing element identified by a valid iterator.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="443"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="444"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This invalidates iterators pointing at the same entry, but erase() returns</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00445" /><CodeLine lineNumber="445"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// an iterator pointing to the next element in the subset&#39;s list. This makes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00446" /><CodeLine lineNumber="446"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// it possible to erase selected elements while iterating over the subset:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00447" /><CodeLine lineNumber="447"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00448" /><CodeLine lineNumber="448"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   tie(I, E) = Set.equal&#95;range(Key);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00449" /><CodeLine lineNumber="449"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   while (I != E)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00450" /><CodeLine lineNumber="450"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///     if (test(&#42;I))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00451" /><CodeLine lineNumber="451"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///       I = Set.erase(I);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00452" /><CodeLine lineNumber="452"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///     else</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00453" /><CodeLine lineNumber="453"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///       ++I;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00454" /><CodeLine lineNumber="454"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00455" /><CodeLine lineNumber="455"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Note that if the last element in the subset list is erased, this will</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00456" /><CodeLine lineNumber="456"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// return an end iterator which can be decremented to get the new tail (if it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00457" /><CodeLine lineNumber="457"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// exists):</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00458" /><CodeLine lineNumber="458"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00459" /><CodeLine lineNumber="459"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  tie(B, I) = Set.equal&#95;range(Key);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00460" /><CodeLine lineNumber="460"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  for (bool isBegin = B == I; !isBegin; /&#42; empty &#42;/) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00461" /><CodeLine lineNumber="461"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    isBegin = (--I) == B;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00462" /><CodeLine lineNumber="462"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    if (test(I))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00463" /><CodeLine lineNumber="463"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///      break;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00464" /><CodeLine lineNumber="464"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    I = erase(I);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00465" /><CodeLine lineNumber="465"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00466" /><CodeLine lineNumber="466" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a3ab390f0c1123852f16664da01de672a"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#ada97379dfb89c01fb4065e33bf180f0e">iterator</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a3ab390f0c1123852f16664da01de672a">erase</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#ada97379dfb89c01fb4065e33bf180f0e">iterator</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
